# Frontend Styling Rules for Vue Components

## CRITICAL RULES: Follow These Exactly for Reliable Styling

### 1. Always Use CSS Variables in Scoped Styles
When styling Vue components with `<style scoped>`, ALWAYS use CSS custom properties (not SCSS variables):

✅ **CORRECT:**
```css
<style scoped>
.my-component {
  color: var(--color-primary);
  padding: var(--spacing-4);
  background: var(--color-background-primary);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-lg);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  transition: var(--transition-base);
}
</style>
```

❌ **WRONG (Don't use SCSS vars in plain scoped CSS):**
```css
<style scoped>
.my-component {
  color: $primary;  /* Won't work without SCSS compilation */
  padding: $spacing-4;
}
</style>
```

### 2. Standard Approach (REQUIRED)
**Always use CSS variables** - they work everywhere and are easier for AI to understand:

```css
<style scoped>
.component {
  /* Colors */
  color: var(--color-primary);
  background: var(--color-background-primary);
  border-color: var(--color-border-light);
  
  /* Spacing */
  padding: var(--spacing-4);
  margin: var(--spacing-8);
  gap: var(--spacing-2);
  
  /* Typography */
  font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
  font-family: var(--font-family-primary);
  line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
  
  /* Borders & Shadows */
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-lg);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
  
  /* Transitions */
  transition: var(--transition-base);
}
</style>
```

### 3. Targeting Child Components (PrimeVue, etc.)
**Always use `:deep()`** to style PrimeVue or child components within scoped styles:

```css
<style scoped>
.parent :deep(.p-button) {
  background: var(--color-primary);
}

.dialog :deep(.p-dialog-header) {
  background: var(--color-primary);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-lg) var(--border-radius-lg) 0 0;
}

/* For complex PrimeVue selectors */
:deep(.p-select-panel),
:deep([data-pc-name="selectpanel"]) {
  background: #ffffff !important;
}
</style>
```

### 4. Variable Reference Guide

**CSS Variables (Use in `<style scoped>` - NO imports needed):**
- Colors: `var(--color-primary)`, `var(--color-text-primary)`, `var(--color-background-primary)`
- Spacing: `var(--spacing-1)` through `var(--spacing-32)`
- Typography: `var(--font-size-xs)` through `var(--font-size-6xl)`, `var(--font-weight-bold)`
- Line Heights: `var(--line-height-tight)`, `var(--line-height-relaxed)`, `var(--line-height-normal)`
- Borders: `var(--border-radius-sm)` through `var(--border-radius-full)`
- Shadows: `var(--shadow-sm)`, `var(--shadow-base)`, `var(--shadow-md)`, `var(--shadow-lg)`, `var(--shadow-xl)`, `var(--shadow-2xl)`
- Transitions: `var(--transition-fast)`, `var(--transition-base)`, `var(--transition-slow)`
- Button Heights: `var(--button-height-sm)`, `var(--button-height-base)`, `var(--button-height-lg)`

### 5. Component Style Block Format

**Standard format (ALWAYS USE THIS):**
```vue
<style scoped>
/* Use CSS variables - no imports needed, works everywhere */
.component-class {
  property: var(--css-variable-name);
}
</style>
```

**DO NOT use SCSS imports in component files:**
❌ `<style scoped lang="scss">` with `@import '../styles/design-tokens';`
✅ `<style scoped>` with CSS variables only

### 6. Where to Add Styles

- **Component-specific styles**: Use `<style scoped>` in the component `.vue` file with CSS variables
- **Global/shared styles**: Add to `frontend/src/styles/styles.scss` (can use SCSS there)
- **PrimeVue theme overrides**: Add to `frontend/src/styles/primevue-orange-theme.scss` (can use SCSS there)
- **Design tokens**: Add to `frontend/src/styles/design-tokens.scss` (SCSS file, but outputs CSS variables)
- **Utility classes**: Add to `frontend/src/styles/utilities.scss` (can use SCSS there)

### 7. Common Patterns

**Hover effects:**
```css
.component:hover {
  transform: translateY(-2px);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
  transition: var(--transition-base);
}
```

**Responsive design:**
```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .component {
    padding: var(--spacing-4);
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
  }
}
```

**PrimeVue component styling:**
```css
.card :deep(.p-card-content) {
  padding: var(--spacing-6);
}

.button-wrapper :deep(.p-button) {
  background: var(--color-primary);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-lg);
}
```

### 8. Mistakes to Avoid

❌ **Don't mix CSS and SCSS variables in component files**
❌ **Don't forget `:deep()` when targeting PrimeVue components**
❌ **Don't use SCSS imports (`@import`) in component `<style scoped>` blocks**
❌ **Don't use `<style scoped lang="scss">` in component files**
❌ **Don't add inline styles when component styles exist**
❌ **Don't use hardcoded colors/values when design tokens exist**

### 9. When Updating Styles

When modifying existing component styles:
1. Use CSS variables (`var(--variable-name)`) - they work everywhere
2. Always use `:deep()` for PrimeVue component overrides
3. Follow the existing pattern in that component file
4. Use design tokens from CSS variables - never hardcode values
5. Keep styles in `<style scoped>` blocks without SCSS imports

### 10. File Locations Reference

- Design tokens: `frontend/src/styles/design-tokens.scss` (SCSS file that defines CSS variables)
- Global styles: `frontend/src/styles/styles.scss` (can use SCSS)
- PrimeVue theme: `frontend/src/styles/primevue-orange-theme.scss` (can use SCSS)
- Utilities: `frontend/src/styles/utilities.scss` (can use SCSS)
- Component styles: In each `.vue` file's `<style scoped>` block (CSS variables only)

### 11. Summary: The Golden Rule

**In Vue component files:**
- ✅ Use `<style scoped>` with CSS variables: `var(--color-primary)`
- ❌ Do NOT use `<style scoped lang="scss">` with SCSS imports
- ❌ Do NOT use SCSS variables like `$primary` in component files

**Only in global SCSS files** (styles.scss, design-tokens.scss, etc.):
- ✅ SCSS variables and imports are allowed
